# Run Locally
The Math3d app is run using the Python `flask` framework with a PostgresSQL database. To run the app locally, first install PostresSQL. Then:

```
$ pip install -r requirements.txt
$ createdb math3d
```

To start the app:

```
python -m local_startup
```

we recommend managing dependencies using [virtualenv](https://virtualenv.pypa.io/en/stable/) and [virtualenvwrapper](http://virtualenvwrapper.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).
